{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3cfdca64-d5a0-407a-b98d-81d58c820453","agentId":"a49c8b65581671737","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are a systems architect researching the cutting edge of SELF-EVOLVING AGENT ARCHITECTURES for a project called the Telos Engine.\n\nThe vision: Agents that have the autonomy to build new agents, train with RL, do self-evolution, and eventually run the whole show — but from a profound intellectual/semantic ground that ensures alignment with universal welfare.\n\nThe current state: dharma_swarm already has 97,000+ lines of working code including a Darwin Engine (evolutionary proposals + fitness scoring + selection), cascade domains (F(S)=S universal loop across code/product/research/skill/meta), 11 telos gates, and 5 autonomy levels.\n\nResearch the frontier:\n\n1. SELF-IMPROVING SYSTEMS (State of the Art):\n- AlphaEvolve (Google DeepMind, 2025): Gemini-powered code evolution that discovered novel algorithms\n- Darwin Gödel Machine (Sakana AI, 2025): Self-improving agents on SWE-bench (20% → 50%)\n- Huxley-Gödel Machine (Schmidhuber, ICLR 2026): Clade Meta-Productivity metric\n- ADAS (Automated Design of Agentic Systems): Meta Agent Search\n- OpenELM: Layer-wise compute allocation\n- What's the cutting edge as of 2026? What works, what doesn't?\n\n2. AGENT-BUILDING-AGENTS:\n- How do you get from \"Darwin Engine proposes code mutations\" to \"agents design and spawn new agents\"?\n- What's the minimal viable architecture for agent autogenesis?\n- How do you prevent the alignment failure of recursive self-improvement?\n- How do telos gates scale as the system self-modifies?\n- What's the role of the constitutional stack (immutable kernel + mutable corpus) in recursive self-improvement?\n\n3. RL FOR AGENT EVOLUTION:\n- How does reinforcement learning integrate with evolutionary search?\n- RLHF vs RLAIF vs constitutional RL — which is appropriate for a telos-aligned system?\n- Can you train agent policies end-to-end on telos-alignment metrics?\n- What reward signals measure \"universal welfare\" (Jagat Kalyan)?\n- How does the R_V metric (geometric contraction in transformer space) serve as a reward signal?\n\n4. THE AUTONOMY SPECTRUM:\n- Current: 5 levels (HUMAN_ONLY → FULLY_AUTONOMOUS)\n- How does the system EARN higher autonomy? What metrics qualify it?\n- Can you define a \"trust ladder\" where the system demonstrates alignment at level N before being granted level N+1?\n- What are the Anduril-style autonomy patterns for civilization-scale systems?\n- How does the VSM (Viable System Model) inform autonomy governance?\n\n5. THE ENDGAME: RUNNING THE SHOW\n- What does \"agents running the whole show\" actually look like?\n- How does a swarm with 100+ specialized agents coordinate without centralization?\n- What's the role of stigmergy (indirect coordination through environment) at massive scale?\n- How do you maintain telos coherence as the system grows from 10 to 100 to 1000 agents?\n- What are the failure modes? How do you prevent goal drift, mesa-optimization, deceptive alignment?\n\nFor each area, provide the most ambitious but grounded 5-year roadmap from current state to full autonomy.\n\nDO NOT write code. ARCHITECTURE RESEARCH ONLY."},"uuid":"c1ca6b1d-5bc7-47dd-b8d5-6747934435bd","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:08.436Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
{"parentUuid":"c1ca6b1d-5bc7-47dd-b8d5-6747934435bd","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a49c8b65581671737","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BNiopFrGexUL5aHzysjiK7","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\n# Telos Engine: Architecture Research for Self-Evolving Agent Systems\n\nI will first examine the current dharma_swarm architecture to ground this research in what actually exists, then synthesize frontier research with architectural recommendations.\n\n---\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\nLet me examine the existing systems that form the foundation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12373,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":12373,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CZ51YSUNCm6a7Sf131JQ8","type":"assistant","uuid":"778beb6c-f27d-4c70-a924-7fb218c577b0","timestamp":"2026-03-15T14:18:12.186Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
